Map blocks
::text
kind: body
Map blocks run Leaflet JS with L, map, and tileLayer globals.
Use them to plot points, shapes, and paths on a dark basemap.
::map
// Leaflet globals: L, map, tileLayer
const points = [
  [40.7484, -73.9857],
  [51.5072, -0.1276],
  [48.8566, 2.3522],
];
points.forEach(([lat, lon]) => {
  L.circleMarker([lat, lon], {
    radius: 5,
    color: '#d0d0d0',
    fillColor: '#d0d0d0',
    fillOpacity: 0.9,
  }).addTo(map);
});
const bounds = L.latLngBounds(points);
map.fitBounds(bounds.pad(0.2));
